Simulate a data entry system. Users will be prompted to enter numeric data. The program will add each item to a list of valid numbers.

If the user enters a non-number, an exception will be thrown, which students must handle. The user is notified of the invalid input, and prompted to continue entering input. All invalid entries are written to another list. 

If the user enters "EXIT", the system prints a goodbye message and exits.

However, if the user enters "ADMIN", they are presented with a chance to enter a password. If they enter the correct password "PASSWORD" they are presented with a menu to view each log of valid and invalid input.

If the user enters the wrong password, an `InvalidPasswordException` (custom exception class) is thrown, and the user is returned to the original numeric entry prompt.
